Miche Avendano-Escobar

About Me:

Hi, I'm Miche Avendano-Escobar, a proud native of Guatemala and a Chicago resident since I was five years old. I identify as agendered and my pronouns are he/they/them. From a young age, I’ve been deeply curious about art, experimenting with various mediums like glass-blowing, pottery, crocheting, and photography. My artistic journey is ever-evolving as I constantly seek new experiences and challenges to fuel my creativity. Whether it's hyperfixating on a single project or diving into something entirely new, I’m driven by a deep passion for making things, which I sometimes attribute to my ADHD. Additionally, you'll always find me watching horror movies or Kdramas, listening to crime podcasts when working on artistic projects. As the middle child in a close-knit family of four siblings (after the passing of my older brother), I’ve learned the importance of adaptability, resilience, and creativity, especially with my older sister moving away for college and leaving me to be the eldest sibling in my household.

As I move forward towards my college experience, I strive to recieve a degree in Entreprenuership and Fine Art studies in order to achieve my dream of owning a tattoo parlour, becoming a tattoo artist, and using my platforms to aide in advocation for minorities like those with disablilities or those in the hispanic community.

Future Aspirations and Plans
After High School, I plan on continuing my studies in college. I will specifically be studying Business (Entrepreneurship) and Art. As I mentioned previously, I want to have my own tattoo parlour and in order to have a successful business, I need to know how to manage it. In addition, I will be studying art to improve on all areas of art so that I may be able to work in any style requested by a costumer. After recieving my diploma, I will head on out to Guatemala to go to a training center for future flight attendants. If all goes well, I'll continue to live in Guatemala while being a flight Attendant for a few years and once I have recieved enough money, deemed by me, I will return to the US and open up my first tattoo parlour.
